What you need to know:

The former Germany forward is expected to sign a three-and-a-half year contract worth five million euros a season with the 19-time Turkish championsThe 32-year-old's anticipated move to Turkey comes after reports in England claimed Ozil and Arsenal had reached an agreement in principle to release him from his contractOzil, who is of Turkish origin, is due to watch Fenerbahce's league game against Ankaragucu on Monday before his unveiling at an elaborate signing ceremony in the coming days